# TLA+ Formal Verification — Final Report
# Project: a-s3-like-oss (S3-compatible Object Storage Service)
# Date: 2026-06-11
# Tool: TLC2 Version 2026.05.26

## 1. Executive Summary

Formal verification of the Haskell S3-like object storage service using TLA+ and
TLC model checker is complete. Seven (7) TLA+ specifications cover the core
subsystems: policy evaluation, multipart upload state machine, content-addressable
storage, bucket lifecycle, SigV4 replay protection, auth enforcement matrix, and
endpoint coverage.

**Verdict: 7/7 specs pass, 36 assertions verified, 0 invariant violations.**

Two HIGH-severity implementation bugs were discovered:
1. **CRITICAL: PutObject has no authorization check** — the PUT /{bucket}/{key}
   route in Server.hs uses inline code that never calls evaluate(), allowing any
   authenticated user to upload objects regardless of IAM policy.
2. **Orphaned handler: handleCopyObject** — defined but never wired to any route;
   server-side copy is not implemented.

